<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Male imago. Length (mm): body, 8.5–9.8; forewing, 8.0–9.8; hind wing, 3.5–4.5; cercus, 22.0–24.0; forelegs lost.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">
Female imago: body, 9.0–12.8; fore wing, 11.7–13.0; hind wing, 4.2–5.0; cercus, 3.7–4.0. Sockets on abdominal sternum VIII formed by long, thin furrow, ending in two separated, but contiguous, sockets (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 146 – 150" captionStartId="40.[151,264,1639,1662]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,195,1618]" captionTargetId="figure@40.[226,1361,195,1618]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURES 146 – 150. C. segnis (specimens from Venezuela): 146, male imago, abdomen, laterodorsal view; 147, female imago, abdomen, d. v.; 148, female head and thorax, v. v. (fs = mesofurcasternum, im = inner margin, p = mesofurcasternal plates, L = middle legs); 149, abdominal sterna (g = gonopore and eggs, sk = sockets, roman numbers = segment number); 150, detail of sockets (arrows indicate socket´s openings)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/838474/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Figs. 149– 150</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,1183,2037]" pageId="37" pageNumber="338">Egg. Length, 320–335 µm; width, 250–260 µm. Yellowish, no polar cap, with small circular, amorphous adhesive structure on convex side.</paragraph>
